\begin_layout Standard
Recall that separation is merely a condition where competitions with 
\begin_inset Formula $\nu$
\end_inset

 are ruled out due to differences in 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

.
 This can result due to extreme differences in 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Psi$
\end_inset

 or
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\nu}$
\end_inset

.
 We consider two representative consumers in the successive bands 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A+\Delta A$
\end_inset

 to see how 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Psi$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\nu}$
\end_inset

 would cause separation.
 First, we consider extreme differences in 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 which cause separation by segmenting the status goods across 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

-bands (
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A+\Delta A$
\end_inset

) and allowing the differences in 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 dominate the comparisons between consumers from band 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A+\Delta A$
\end_inset

.
 Next we consider how 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\nu}$
\end_inset

 differences could cause a separation.
 Here, if 
\begin_inset Formula $\Psi$
\end_inset

 didn't change across successive bands 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A+\Delta A$
\end_inset

 for the two consumers from the respective bands who also have the same
 total expenditure 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 i.e.
 if 
\begin_inset Formula $\Psi(A)=\Psi(A+\Delta A)$
\end_inset

 then a higher 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\nu}(A+\Delta A)$
\end_inset

 in the band 
\begin_inset Formula $A+\Delta A$
\end_inset

 i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\nu}(A+dA)>P_{\nu}(A)$
\end_inset

 prevents a separation since 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{x-\Psi(A)-\delta}{P_{\nu}(A+dA)}<\frac{x-\Psi(A)-\delta}{P_{\nu}(A)}$
\end_inset

 and the indifference 
\begin_inset Formula $u(\frac{x-\Psi(A)-\delta}{P_{\nu}(A)},A)=u(\frac{x-\Psi(A)-\delta}{P_{\nu}(A+\Delta A)},A+\Delta A)$
\end_inset

 could be possible.
 In other words, the consumers could exchange places with each other if
 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\nu}(A+\Delta A)>P_{\nu}(A)$
\end_inset

.
 Conversely, if we find a substitution in the successive bands i.e.
 consumers reducing the excesses (facing the same 
\begin_inset Formula $\Psi$
\end_inset

 across the band) as they move to the band 
